Sure, let’s take a look at Genesis 37 and see what happens if we read every third line. This chapter is about Joseph, his dreams, and the beginning of his journey into Egypt. By pulling out every third line, we might find an interesting pattern or a hidden layer of meaning.

### **Genesis 37 (Every Third Line Extraction)**

1. **Verse 1:** &quot;Jacob lived in the land where his father had stayed, the land of Canaan.&quot;
2. **Verse 4:** &quot;When his brothers saw that their father loved him more than any of them, they hated him and could not speak a kind word to him.&quot;
3. **Verse 7:** &quot;We were binding sheaves of grain out in the field when suddenly my sheaf rose and stood upright, while your sheaves gathered around mine and bowed down to it.&quot;
4. **Verse 10:** &quot;When he told his father as well as his brothers, his father rebuked him and said, &#x27;What is this dream you had? Will your mother and I and your brothers actually come and bow down to the ground before you?&#x27;&quot;
5. **Verse 13:** &quot;And Israel said to Joseph, &#x27;As you know, your brothers are grazing the flocks near Shechem. Come, I am going to send you to them.&#x27; &#x27;Very well,&#x27; he replied.&quot;
6. **Verse 16:** &quot;He replied, &#x27;I’m looking for my brothers. Can you tell me where they are grazing their flocks?&#x27;&quot;
7. **Verse 19:** &quot;&#x27;Here comes that dreamer!&#x27; they said to each other.&quot;
8. **Verse 22:** &quot;‘Don’t shed any blood,’ Reuben said. &#x27;Throw him into this cistern here in the wilderness, but don’t lay a hand on him.&#x27; Reuben said this to rescue him from them and take him back to his father.&quot;
9. **Verse 25:** &quot;As they sat down to eat their meal, they looked up and saw a caravan of Ishmaelites coming from Gilead. Their camels were loaded with spices, balm, and myrrh, and they were on their way to take them down to Egypt.&quot;
10. **Verse 28:** &quot;So when the Midianite merchants came by, his brothers pulled Joseph up out of the cistern and sold him for twenty shekels of silver to the Ishmaelites, who took him to Egypt.&quot;
11. **Verse 31:** &quot;Then they got Joseph’s robe, slaughtered a goat and dipped the robe in the blood.&quot;
12. **Verse 34:** &quot;Then Jacob tore his clothes, put on sackcloth and mourned for his son many days.&quot;
